    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="2. CEREBROSPINAL MENINGITIS (CSM) 2.1 In the reporting week, 21 suspected Cerebrospinal Meningitis (CSM) cases with one laboratory confirmed and one death (CFR, 4.8%) were reported from 14 LGAs in nine States(Ebonyi – 1, Gombe – 1, Kaduna – 2, Katsina – 4, Kebbi – 6, Ondo – 2, Sokoto – 1, Taraba - 1 &amp; Zamfara – 3) compared with 87 suspected cases and three deaths (CFR, 3.4%) reported across 41 LGAs (16 States) at the same period in 2018 (Figure 1) 2.2 Between weeks 1 and 6 (2019), 173 suspected meningitis cases with nine laboratory confirmed and eight deaths (CFR, 4.62%) from 75 LGAs (20 States) were reported compared with 557 suspected cases with 71 Laboratory confirmed and 37 deaths (CFR, 6.64%) from 122 LGAs in 24 states during the same period in 2018"/>
